== Mashed Potatoes ==

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{} or @?water{}. Mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Cover to keep warm.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Cajun Chicken ==

Meanwhile, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cook until browned, shifting occasionally, ~{5-6%minutes}. -- IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once chicken is browned, add garlic and @Cajun spice mix{2%sachets} and fry for ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

== Creamy Cajun Sauce ==

Stir in the @passata{1%pack}, @chicken stock{1%sachet} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (double for 4p).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer until chicken is cooked through ~{4-5%minutes}. -- IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir through the @creme fraiche{65%g} and @grated Italian style hard cheese{1%unit}.

Add the @baby spinach{60%g} to the pan, a handful at a time and cook, stirring until wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Loosen the sauce with a splash of @water{to taste} if necessary.

== To Serve ==

When everything is ready, divide the creamy Cajun chicken between #bowls{}.

Serve the creamy mash alongside.